Critical writer, Kakwenza Rukirabashaija has arrived in Germany, two weeks after going into exile. Kakwenza who was detained for two weeks and later charged with offensive communication for allegedly abusing President Yoweri Museveni and his son Muhoozi Kainerugaba, an army boss. The 33-year-old who was awarded the international writer of courage PEN Prize, was arrested in December 2021 at his home in Kampala and detained at an unknown place. Speaking after his release, Rukirabashaija described how he had been tortured while in detention by the Special Forces Command. The writer was charged withÂ offensive communication contrary to section 25 of the Computer Misuse Act 2011 for allegedly abusing President Museveni and his son through social media. He joins political activist and academic Stella Nyanzi who left the country, claiming political persecution and threats on her life.